<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-337-614  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 337 614.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  April 9 1990 v7 n14 p3(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DEC grants LAT license to 3Com for multiprotocol terminal server.andO;(local area transport) (3Com's new CS2000, CS2100 communicationsservers) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Smalley, Eric.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>3Com Corp will become the second firm to license Local AreaTerminal (LAT) technology from DEC for use on its low-endcommunications servers.andP;  3Com's $2,800 CS2000 and its $3,300CS2100 communications servers are 10-port machines powered by12-MHz Motorola 68000 microprocessors with 1Mbyte of memory.andP;  Eachof the ports can provide a data rate as high as 38.4Kbps and anEthernet interface is included.andP;  The CS2000 is a diskless server,while the CS2100 comes with a 3.5-inch floppy disk drive.andP;  3Comdecided to license the technology from DEC even though many othervendors are offering reverse engineered LAT products becausecustomer confidence will be higher with DEC's blessings.andP;  3Comalso states that DEC plans to strongly enforce its LAT patent inthe future.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Digital Equipment Corp. (licenses)3Com Corp. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    COMS; DEC.andO;Product:   3Com CS/2000 (File server) (product introduction)3Com CS/2100 (File server) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     LicensingFile ServersProtocolStandardsCommunications Equipment.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>DEC grants LAT license to 3Com for multiprotocol terminal serverandM;SANTA CLARA, Calif.andP;  -- While many Local Area Transport (LAT) terminal servervendors have expanded their horizons by adding support for TCP/IP, 3Com iscoming at the same market from the other direction.andM;3Com announced last week that DEC has granted it a LAT license.andP;  The companyalso introduced low-end communications servers to which it will add LATsupport by the end of this year or early next year.andM;The 10-port CS2000-series communications servers are available now withsupport for TCP/IP, XNS or Open Systems Interconnect protocols.andM;3Com joins Cisco Systems of Menlo Park, Calif., in licensing LAT for use withterminal server products.andP;  Terminal server vendors using reverse-engineeredLAT software have resisted licensing the protocol from dEC because of thehigh per-port royalty fee ($15 per port per server), details of the licensingprogram and concerns about DEC's enforcement of the LAT patents.andP;  (See &quot;Ciscosigns first LAT license for use in multiprotocol server,&quot; DR, April 2, page4.)andM;Customer confidence and ensured compatibility with DEC's LAT implementationoutweigh the costs of licensing LAT from DEC, said Bill Lozoff, 3Com productmanager.andP;  DEC officials have assured 3Com that once certain patent issues areresolved, DEC will strongly enforce the LAT patents, according to Lozoff.andM;3Com will implement LAT in a concurrent LAT-TCP/IP communication server andis considering developing a combined LAT-TCP/IP-OSI product, said SaraRadicati, 3Com's product line manager.andM;The company also plans to implement the SLIP and SNMP protocols at a laterdate, she said.andM;The CS2000 and CS2100 communications servers currently support one protocolat a time.andM;The CS2000-series servers are powered by a 12MHz Motorola 68000microprocessor and 1MB of memory.andP;  The servers offer an aggregate throughputof 192Kbits per second (Kbps), according to Radicati.andM;Each port can be set to provide a data rate as high as 38.4Kbps.andM;The servers have 10 RS232-c ports and an Ethernet interface.andP;  The Ethernetinterface can support coaxial, twisted-pair of fiber-optic cable.andM;The CS2000 is a diskless server that boots from 3Com's Network ControlService network management station.andP;  The CS2100 includes a 3-1/2-inch floppydisk drive.andM;The CS2000 series supports synchronous and asynchronous communications on all10 ports and includes modem support.andM;The CS2000 is priced at $2,800, and the CS2100 is priced at $3,300.andM;3Com Corp. can be contacted at 3165 Kifer Road, Santa Clara, CA 95052-8145,(800) 638-3266.andO;</TEXT></DOC>